The long sleeves make it suitable for slightly cooler weather, ensuring you stay comfortable.

Wardrobe Essential: Are you still struggling to find the perfect fall fashion staple? Look no further! Our Long sleeve shirt is your ultimate choice. This monochromatic approach makes it an ideal choice for versatile pairings, effortlessly complementing various bottoms such as cargo pants, jeans, and more.

Occasion: Whether you're dressing for a casual outing or a formal event, this basic tee showcases its versatility, allowing you to confidently express your fashion sense in any setting, such as work, a party, a club, travel.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Dup for Skims
reviews.reviewText: All of these shirts fit so nice, I got an XS and is true to size. There is a great balance of material that is smooth and tight yet I don’t feel restricted. The colors are true to the online images. Reasonable price and great quality. I might have to get more of them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: DUPE ALERT!!! This is a great dupe for both Skims and Aritzia/Babaton. They are so soft and double-lined so everything is smoothed out. It's both stretchy and supportive. No sheerness since it is double-lined. It's a good length too! It can be worn right at the waist (depending on torso length, mine is slightly longer than average) or it still looks cute if scrunched up for a more cropped look. I bought this in 3 colors and definitely going to order more!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars SOFT BUTTER HEAVEN
reviews.reviewText: they can bury me in this shirt. It is INSANELY butter soft. It’s also the perfect material it’s not even a little bit see through. It’s nice and stretchy too. Honestly if you’re considering buying it, just do it. 10/10.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Comfortable and flattering, material very similar to skims
reviews.reviewText: For reference, I am 5’7, 120kbs and ordered 4 shirts, 2 XS and 2 S. A lot of times when I order shirts on amazon, even the XS’s will be too big or shaped for spongebob squarepants. These shirts fit me really nice and are very comfortable. The XS is just a tad too short for my long torso as I like to tuck my shirts into my pants and the XS I have to tuck in every so often as its not long enough to in. My skims do this too though and its not a deal breaker. The S’s definitely have a bit more room and Im able to stretch it enough to where I like. Like many have said, the sleeves are on the shorter side BUT I do not mind this as I hate when sleeves are so long they cover my hand or feel restricted. I do recommend this shirt and hope this review helps those similar in height/weight as I took a chance on these not knowing what to expect. Worth the cost for half the price of skims. I only wish they came in more colors.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My new fav!!
reviews.reviewText: I love this shirt!!! It’s not a total skims dupe but it’s very good in its own way. It’s double lined, buttery soft and just a perfect shirt that can be dressed up or down. I read reviews abt the sizing and sized up to S, normally an XS, and it fit great. For reference I’m 5”0 & 125. Definitely a closet staple !

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars 3x is a size 24 MAX
reviews.reviewText: These tops are somewhat plus size friendly and I almost bought one in a color because they only go up to XXL and I'm glad I didn't. The 3x will fit a size 24 plus size max and that's if you don't mind a crop. They are SUPER soft and I plan on ordering more in the black color, but these are super short. If you have a large bust (I'm 48DD) they will JUST fit you. I also have a long torso, these JUST hit my high waisted leggings. I'm also 5'8" for height reference. I love these tops, but I hope in the future they come out with a 4x and more colors for the plus sizes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I do love this top and I enjoy wearing it! Although I am going to say something negative about it on a personal level, something that I wasn't thinking about and as you can see it's got nothing to do with how I rated the product. On me the arms are a little tight, or perhaps I should say snug, and I seem to be pulling on the sleeves a lot. Although by doing that the material has a tendency to grab my hair on my arms and give it a discomfort feeling. It doesn't hurt and it does not pitch and I think it's just indicative to any kind of material that fits snug around the arms.Maybe I'm just being a big sissy, although I think I'm going to trim my hair on my arms just a little bit before I wear it the next time. Anyhow I had the same problem with a pair of underarmor compression top that I had. Anyhow just something to think about, all in all I give it a thumbs up, the material is nice and soft and it has a four-way stretch

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this! True to size.
reviews.reviewText: Love this, this is my favorite brand to buy long sleeves from & basic shirts from. The fabric is so buttery, thick, stretchy and flattering. I have these shirts in almost every color now! 🥰
Love this brand buy the Canadian price is pretty high ....Worth it. We need a Canadian supplier of this brand cause I'm tired of waiting 3 weeks fir delivery and paying close to SKIMmmmms costs.

Great quality, very thick and double lined. I usually order size small in clothes but I think the size small was too big. It was too loose in the armpits and stomach and bunched up. It also got dyed pink in the wash, so make sure to separate colours while washing. It is great for winter and layering under sweaters, and wearing on its own. I would size down.

I’m 5’3 124lbs, I ordered a small in Marsala. it fits perfect, and the colour is nice. The reason this shirt isn’t worth the $50 Canadian is that I wore it once and it began to pill immediately all over the sleeves.

I have been on the hunt for a non see-through white long sleeves shirt and based on the reviews I really thought I had finally found it ! However, I am actually disappointed because although the overall quality is nice and the fabric is buttery soft, the sleeves are not double-lined and it shows the difference in color between the bodice and the sleeves. Additionnally, although I sized up and ordered a large intead of my regular medium size, the sleeves are too short and are riding up. For reference I am 5'8" 135 lbs slim build. Sadly returning and the hunt continues....
